<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7732] [89-fb] Make HFileWriter use the bytesPerChecksum obtained from config</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7732</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;we found a bug in the latest HBase code which &quot;hfile.io.bytes.per.checksum&quot; does not take effect. Because we have never call HFile.getBytesPerChecksum()  when creating a HFile.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix this issue by calling the correct bytes/checksum (from HFile.getBytesPerChecksum) for HFile creating ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12630220">HBASE-7732</key>
            <summary>[89-fb] Make HFileWriter use the bytesPerChecksum obtained from config</summary>
